This directory vendors a prebuilt copy of libheif-js for in-browser HEIC
decoding in the Image Converter tool.

Components and licenses:

- libheif — the underlying HEIF/HEIC decoding library (C), compiled to
  JavaScript (ASM.js) via Emscripten.
  Copyright (c) struktur AG and contributors.
  Licensed under the GNU Lesser General Public License v3.0 (LGPL-3.0).
  Source: https://github.com/strukturag/libheif
  Full license text: see ./LICENSE (LGPL-3.0, which incorporates the
  GNU GPL-3.0 by reference: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt).

- libheif-js — the npm packaging/build wrapper. Version 1.19.8.
  Licensed under LGPL-3.0 (per its npm metadata; it bundles libheif).
  Source: https://github.com/catdad-experiments/libheif-js

The file `libheif.js` is the unmodified vendored ASM.js build obtained via
`npm pack libheif-js@1.19.8`, with a short ESM export shim appended at the
end (clearly marked). It is served from this site's own origin; nothing is
sent to a third party.
